            <title>[PIG-461] Limit produces results in the wrong order</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-461</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Script:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A = load &apos;studenttab200m&apos; as (name, age, gpa);&lt;br/&gt;
B = filter A by age &amp;gt; 20;&lt;br/&gt;
C = group B by name;&lt;br/&gt;
D = foreach C generate group, COUNT(B) PARALLEL 16;&lt;br/&gt;
E = order D by $0 PARALLEL 16;&lt;br/&gt;
F = limit E 10;&lt;br/&gt;
--explain F;&lt;br/&gt;
dump F;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;comes out not sorted on the name&lt;/p&gt;</description>
